-- Mexico Reports 4.3 Billion Peso Budget Surplus Through Feb.
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   R o e d e r
-- 2012-03-30T21:07:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/mexico-reports-4-3-billion-peso-budget-surplus-through-feb-1-.html
Mexico  posted a budget surplus of
4.3 billion pesos ($336 million) in February excluding
investment by state oil company Petroleos Mexicanos, the  Finance
Ministry  said today in an e-mailed statement.  Including investment by Pemex, as the state oil company is
known, Mexico had a deficit of 24.3 billion pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Roeder in Mexico City at 
